---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout pageTitle="Shakia Williams - Textile Art" customFavicon="/images/Mrs_Annies_Nience.jpg">
  <a href="/gallery/" style="margin:1rem;display:inline-block;">← Back to Gallery</a>
    <main class="artist-page-bg" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto;">
      
      <h1 style="color: #ffa500; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Shakia Williams</h1>
      
      <picture>
        <source srcset="/images/Mrs_Annies_Nience.webp" type="image/webp" />
        <img 
          src="/images/Mrs_Annies_Nience.jpg" 
          alt="Shakia Williams Textile Portrait" 
          style="width:100%; max-width:600px; display:block; margin:1rem auto; border-radius:12px;" 
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
        />
      </picture>
      
      <section style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 2rem; margin-top:2rem; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center;">
        <img src="/images/artists/mrs_annies_nience/profile.jpg" alt="Artist Profile" style="width:180px; height:180px; border-radius:50%; object-fit:cover; box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); flex-shrink: 0;" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
        <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
          <h2 style="color: #ffa500; margin-top: 0;">About the Artist</h2>
          <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff;">
            This fabric portrait was created by an artist whose creative journey spans multiple disciplines and decades. Their first 
            fascination was fashion design in high school, until all their designs disappeared. This setback led them to explore 
            interior design, which then shifted to fine art encompassing painting, drawing, sculpture, crafts, and jewelry.
          </p>
          <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff; margin-top: 1rem;">
            A graduate of Michigan State University with a BFA earned in 1974, the artist moved to California and taught art for one 
            year before deciding to pursue another credential in Special Education Communication Handicapped. They dedicated 30 years 
            to teaching special education while still incorporating art into their career as much as possible, demonstrating a lifelong 
            commitment to both creativity and education.
          </p>
          <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff; margin-top: 1rem;">
            Some time ago, they learned quilting and fabric portraits, truly enjoying the creative aspect as much as the other art 
            forms they've practiced over the years. Their creative level never stops escalating, and this textile portrait represents 
            the latest evolution in a remarkable artistic journey that has spanned fashion, interior design, fine arts, education, 
            and now fabric portraiture.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      
      <section style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h2 style="color: #ffa500;">About the Subject</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff;">
          This portrait depicts Shakia Williams, Mrs. Annie's niece, celebrating family connections and honoring the bonds that 
          unite us across generations. The work represents not just a family member, but the enduring relationships and wisdom 
          passed down through family lines, preserving memories and stories through the art of fabric portraiture.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h2 style="color: #ffa500;">About the Artwork</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff;">
          This textile portrait brings together the artist's decades of experience across multiple art forms—from fashion design 
          and interior design to painting, sculpture, and crafts. The piece demonstrates how their BFA training from Michigan State 
          University and 30 years of teaching experience combine with their more recent exploration of quilting and fabric portraits.
        </p>
        <p style="line-height: 1.6; color: #fff; margin-top: 1rem;">
          The work reflects the artist's philosophy that creativity never stops escalating. Each stitch and fabric choice draws from 
          a lifetime of artistic exploration, showing how diverse creative experiences enrich and inform new artistic endeavors. This 
          portrait stands as testament to the artist's unwavering dedication to creative expression throughout their remarkable career.
        </p>
      </section>
      
  </main>
</Layout>
